Privacy Policy
Last updated: 01/19/2025
This Privacy Policy ("Policy") explains how Remedy Apps LLC ("Remedy Apps," "we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and protects your personal information when you use the Lazy Bear application ("App") and our website ("Website"). By using the App or accessing the Website, you consent to the practices described in this Policy.
Information We Collect
Personal Information: We may collect personal information that you voluntarily provide to us, such as your name, email address, age, fitness goals, and demographic information when you register an account, complete your profile, or communicate with us.
Health and Fitness Data: The App may collect health and fitness-related data, including activity tracking, workout history, and goals, either entered manually or synced through third-party devices or services like fitness trackers.
Device Information: The App and Website may collect certain device information automatically, including your IP address, device type, operating system, and mobile network information.
Use of Information
We use the collected information to improve the functionality of the App, personalize your fitness experience, offer tailored workout recommendations, track progress, and communicate with you.
Your personal information may also be used for analyzing user trends, tracking App usage, and gathering statistical information to enhance our understanding of user preferences and improve our services.
Anonymized and aggregated data may be used for advertising and promotional purposes, such as displaying relevant fitness tips, challenges, or health-related content.
Data Sharing and Disclosure
Service Providers: We may share your personal information with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in operating the App and Website, conducting business, or providing services to you. These service providers are obligated to maintain the confidentiality and security of your personal information.
Legal Requirements: We may disclose your personal information if required by law, to protect our rights or the rights of others, or in response to a valid legal request.
No Sale of Information: We will never sell your personal information to third parties.
Data Retention
We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Policy or as required by law. Once your information is no longer needed, we will securely delete or anonymize it.
Data Security
We implement appropriate security measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.
However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your information.
Children's Privacy
The App and Website are not intended for use by individuals under the age of 16. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you become aware that a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us, and we will take steps to remove the information promptly.
Your Rights
Access, Correction, and Deletion: You have the right to access, correct, update, or delete your personal information. You can exercise these rights by accessing your account settings in the App or by contacting us.
Additional Rights: Depending on your jurisdiction, you may also have additional rights, such as the right to restrict processing or the right to data portability. We will make reasonable efforts to respond to your requests in a timely manner.
Third-Party Services
The App and Website may include links to third-party websites or services. This Policy does not apply to those third-party platforms. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of those platforms before providing any personal information.
We use third-party programs and APIs, such as fitness tracker integrations and analytics tools, to enhance the functionality of the App and Website. These third-party services may collect and process your personal information in accordance with their own privacy policies.
International Transfers
Your personal information may be transferred to and processed in countries outside of your jurisdiction, where data protection laws may differ. By using the App and accessing the Website, you consent to such transfers.
Subscriptions and In-App Purchases
We offer subscriptions and in-app purchases through the Google Play Store and the Apple App Store. The collection and processing of your personal information related to these subscriptions and purchases are subject to the respective platforms' terms and privacy policies. We do not collect or store payment information directly. For more information on how these platforms handle your personal data, please refer to their privacy policies.
User-Generated Content
The App may allow users to post content, such as fitness progress updates, comments, or other materials. Please be aware that any content you post is publicly accessible, and we cannot control how others may use or share that information. We encourage you to post only content that is appropriate, legal, and in compliance with our
Terms of Service
.
Additional Information
We may use third-party payment processors, such as Stripe, to facilitate subscription payments. The collection and processing of payment information by these processors are subject to their respective privacy policies and terms of service.
Compliance with GDPR, CCPA, and Other Applicable Laws
We strive to comply with applicable data protection laws, including the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), and other relevant regulations. If you are a resident of the European Economic Area (EEA) or California, you may have specific rights and protections regarding your personal information. Please refer to the "Your Rights" section for more details on exercising these rights.
Changes to this Policy
We reserve the right to update or modify this Policy at any time. We will notify you of any material changes by posting the updated Policy on the App or through other means. Your continued use of the App and access to the Website after any modifications to the Policy constitutes your acceptance of the revised Policy.
Contact Us
If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or the App and Website, please contact us at
support.lazybear@startremedy.com
.
This Privacy Policy applies to information collected through the Lazy Bear App and Website. By using the App and accessing the Website, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agreed to the terms of this Policy.